{
  "text": "On the other hand, the entanglement spectrum [CITATION_1] obtained via ED in the spherical geometry [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and the DMRG method in the infinite cylindrical geometry [CITATION_4] provides evidence supporting that the 7/3 state has the Laughlin-type edge excitation spectrum. It was argued [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] that the apparent discrepancy between the low ground-state overlap and the Laughlin-type entanglement spectrum could be caused by the fact that quasiparticles/holes in the 7/3 state are very large. Large quasiparticles/holes can be well captured by the variational Monte Carlo simulation [CITATION_7] as well as the DMRG method [CITATION_8] , while not by ED using relatively small finitesize systems.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "23453061",
